    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. you're talking a lot about the chaos that followed, but some people argue that the failure wasn't the intervention itself, but rather the lack of a long-term commitment to actually build stable institutions afterward. wouldn't you say they had a moral obligation to stay and fix what they broke, or is the whole idea of intervening to promote democracy inherently flawed?",
