      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The idea that Western powers have a moral obligation to stay and fix broken states is a dangerous fallacy that ignores the reality of national sovereignty and the limits of foreign intervention. Promoting democracy through military force is inherently flawed because it assumes a level of political maturity and institutional capacity that simply does not exist in most post-conflict societies. History shows that without genuine local ownership and a clear, sustainable strategy, external actors will inevitably fail, leaving the region more unstable than before.",
      "source": "target",
